                                                                  7735 1451
  General methodology: The global approach considered in this     7735 1451
          work is presented in the following paper: Modern        7735 1451
          nuclear data evaluation with the TALYS code system,     7735 1451
          A.J. Koning and D. Rochman, Nuclear Data Sheets 113     7735 1451
          (2012) 2841.                                            7735 1451
                                                                  7735 1451
  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           7735 1451
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         7735 1451
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR7735 1451
       expands from 0 to 1.621708E+3 eV. A total of               7735 1451
       2 l-values are used and 200 resonances. The resonance      7735 1451
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              7735 1451
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       7735 1451
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          7735 1451
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     7735 1451
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    7735 1451
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  7735 1451
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   7735 1451
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          7735 1451
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       7735 1451
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    7735 1451
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       7735 1451
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         7735 1451
       The s-wave average level spacing is 3.028 eV and           7735 1451
       the s-wave neutron strength is 0.0001406 1e-4.             7735 1451
                                                                  7735 1451
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  7735 1451
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    7735 1451
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    7735 1451
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   7735 1451
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    7735 1451
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              7735 1451
